<section id="about" class="section">
    <div class="pizza-plain">{% image "static/img/pizza-plain.webp", "" %}</div>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Us</h1>
        <p>
            Founded by Danny Seiden (<a href="https://instagram.com/breadwinepizza">@breadwinepizza</a>), Tony Colasacco
            (<a href="https://instagram.com/incarbzwetrust">@incarbzwetrust</a>), and Chris Bracco (<a
                href="https://instagram.com/braccobreadco"
                >@braccobreadco</a
            >), The Pizza Project is a pizza pop-up showcase currently hosted on Sundays at Montclair Bread Company in
            Montclair, New Jersey.
        </p>
        <p>
            What began as an friendly exchange of dough recipes and pizza photos on Instagram quickly grew into a shared
            dream of bringing their creations to life for the public to enjoy. After helping Chris with his brewery and
            festival pizza pop-ups in 2024, the trio found themselves energized by each other’s creativity and the
            possibilities of baking beyond their home kitchens.
        </p>
        <p>
            Now they’re on a mission to scale up their own creations and showcase the talents of other at-home pizza
            artisans in hopes of building a vibrant community of pizza makers and pizza lovers.
        </p>
        <p>
            What sets The Pizza Project apart is a commitment to creativity, community, and quality, with the goal of
            inspiring and engaging pizza lovers of all kinds. From crispy sourdough New York-style pies to fluffy
            Detroit squares to charred New Haven slices and more, each pizza tells a story of technique, flavor, and
            cultural relevance. To us, there is no greater joy than creating and enjoying a delicious slice of pizza
            with fellow enthusiasts.
        </p>
        <p>
            Plans are underway for more pop-ups and showcases, as well as dough-making classes, hosting private parties
            and events, and more. The Pizza Project isn’t just a one-time treat: it’s an invitation to a community
            pursuing well-crafted pizza. Please join us and follow along for updates!
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
